  "texts": [
    "The key insight of their discovery was that the two strands were held together by hydrogen bonds between complementary pairs of nitrogenous bases: adenine (A) always pairs with thymine (T), and cytosine (C) always pairs with guanine (G).",
    "Significance: The discovery of the structure of DNA revolutionized the fields of biology and genetics.",
    "It provided the key to understanding how genetic information is stored and replicated.",
    "Some of the profound implications include: 1.",
    "Understanding Heredity: The double helix structure of DNA explained how genetic information is passed from one generation to the next."
  ]
}